    <bioghist>In 1941 the University of Michigan established a heredity clinic under the direction of Lee R. Dice. James V. Neel served as director of the genetics clinic from 1956 until 1993. Clinic work evolved from the study of hereditary traits and diseases and grew to include genetic counseling.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Clinic records primarily contain kindred files of subjects studied at the clinic. The files were utilized by staff for several intensive studies leading to breakthroughs in the study of diseases including neurofibromatosis and sickle cell anemia. Indexes, negatives, and slides comprise the remainder of the material.</scopecontent>
